<http://dx.doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2014.100>
    bibo:endPage "75" ;
    bibo:issue "100" ;
    bibo:journal "European Journal of Taxonomy" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2014-10-24" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    dc:creator "Enghoff, Henrik" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "A mountain of millipedes I: An endemic species-group of the genus Chaleponcus Attems, 1914, from the Udzungwa Mountains, Tanzania (Diplopoda, Spirostreptida, Odontopygidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860508>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860472>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860466>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860470> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860508>
    dc:description "Fig. 27. Chaleponcus termini sp. nov., gonopods. A. Right gonopod, posterior view. B. Right gonopod, anterior view. C. Left telopodite, mesal-ventral view. D. Left coxite, mesal view. E. Right telopodite, anterior-ventral view. al1, al2 = anterior telomeral lobe, cu = cucullus, mf = metaplical flange, ms = metaplical shelf, mss = metaplical shelf-spine, pl = posterior telomeral lamella, ps = proximal spine on solenomere. Scales 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3860508/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860472>
    dc:description "Fig. 9. Chaleponcus spp., outline of coxite of left gonopod, posterior view. (The ’transverse’ plane of the gonopod is usually slightly at angles with the exact transverse plane of the millipede, so it may be necessary to tilt the gonopod slightly in order to obtain the view shown on the drawings.) The stippled lines indicate the place where the telopodital basomere emerges from the coxal cavity. Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3860472/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860466>
    dc:description "Fig. 7. Gonopod coxa terminology, left coxa of Chaleponcus termini sp. nov., mesal(-posterior) view. cu = cucullus, mf = anteriad metaplical flange, mfp = metaplical flange process, ms = metaplical shelf, mss = metaplical shelf-spine, prl = proplical lobe." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3860466/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860470>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Gonopod telopodite terminology. — A. Left telopodite of Chaleponcus termini sp. nov., posterior view. White oval = basomere, blue oval = torsotope, red oval = telomere, yellow = solenomere (slm), green = proximal spine of solenomere (ps), pxl = proximal lobe of telomere, st = main stem of telomere, st’ = shallow lobe of st. B–C. Torsotope (left gonopod) with torsotope process (tp). B. C. vilici sp. nov., mesal-anterior view. C. C. netus sp. nov., posterior view. D. Solenomere (C. dabagaensis) to show longitudinal fluting. E. Tip of solenomere (C. netus sp. nov.) to show spinulation. Scales: 0.1 mm (A– D), 0.01 mm (E)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3860470/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

